In the MATTER OF the Petition for REINSTATEMENT OF Dana PAUL to the Bar of Maryland Misc. Docket AG No. 9, Sept. Term, 2018 Court of Appeals of Maryland. August 9, 2018

ORDER

Upon consideration of the Petition for Reinstatement of Dana Paul and the responses filed thereto, in the above captioned case, it is this 9th day of August, 2018,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, a majority of the Court concurring, that the petition be, and it is hereby, GRANTED, and the petitioner, Dana Paul, be, and is hereby, reinstated to the practice of law in this State; and it is further

ORDERED, that the Clerk of the Court shall replace the name of Dana Paul upon the register of attorneys entitled to practice law in this State and certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund and the Clerks of all judicial tribunals in this state.

Judge Greene did not participate in the consideration of this matter.
